SixesWildGame.model

Class Square

  • java.lang.Object
    • SixesWildGame.model.Square
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class Square
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    Square - this Object will be the building blocks to a Board, and can contain a Tile which can be used to a Move If a Square is inert, then it cannot be selected and it cannot contain a Tile.
    Author:
    Alex

      • Square

        public Square(int r,
      int c,
      int i)
        Constructor of an inert or a goal Square. This is a Square whose a Tile cannot be added and it cannot be marked, or a square which is a goal in release.
        Parameters:
        r - - Row location of the Square
        c - - Column location of the Square
        i - - the value which determines the isInert and isSixesGoal values. A value of 1 sets only isInert to true. a value of 2 will set isInert to true and isSixesGoal to true if the Square's column is 8. Any other value will set both isInert and isSixesGoal to false

      • getTile

        public Tile getTile()
        Removes the Tile from the Square, and changes the Tile's parent to null. This is much like Pile.get() from A1. Note: if the Square does not currently have a Tile, it just returns null and does not change the Square. Note #2: if the Square is inert, then it should not have a Tile, but return null anyways
        Returns:
        this.tile

      • peekTile

        public Tile peekTile()
        Does not change the Square-Tile relationship, but returns a new Tile which has the same data as the tile located in the Square. This is much like Pile.peek() from A1
        Returns:
        this.tile

      • equals

        public boolean equals(Square other)
        equals() - an override of whether or not the current Square and the given Square are the same. This method simply checks whether or not they have the same row and column location, as well as Tile, isMarked, and isInert be changed at a later time depending on usage
        Parameters:
        other -
        Returns:
        whether or not the two Squares have the same location, Tile, and isMarked value

      • getTileColor

        public java.awt.Color getTileColor()
        return the color of the Tile located in the current Square. If there is no Tile, return Black If the Square is inert, also return Black, but throw an error
        Returns:
        color of the Tile

      • getTileValue

        public int getTileValue()
        get the value of the Tile located in the current Square. If there is no Tile, return 0. Also, if the Square is inert, return 0
        Returns:
        value of the Tile
